[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 Nbd7 7. Qe2
{ One of the most dangerous moves. In this line, Black needs to know a lot, but what I like about the whole 6... Nbd7 line is that Black also has a good chance of playing for a win. There are not many forced draws. In this line, in order to fight for an advantage, White must take risks. }
7... h6
{ One of the most principled continuations. The other option is  7...e6  8.f4  Qc7  which transposes to the line @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/1p2pppp/p2p1n2/6B1/3NP3/2N5/PPP2PPP/R2QKB1R b - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  6...e6  7.f4  Nbd7  . }
8. Bh4
{ Clearly the critical move. For now White wants to keep his bishop in the game. }
8... g6
{ The point of Black's previous move. Black definitely wants to meet f4 with ....e5! }
9. f4
{ This is the critical move. The whole line is very double-edged. Both sides should be very well prepared. }
9... e5 { The usual response to f2-f4. } 10. fxe5 dxe5 11. O-O-O
{ The most critical line. } 11... Qc7
{ Now  11...exd4?  is very bad in view of  12.e5  and White wins. } 12. Nb3
{ The other move are worse, for example,  12.Nf3  b5  and Black gets very good counterplay. }
12... b5
{ We've arrived at the critical position for the whole 7. Qe2 line. White has many different options here. According to my analysis, though, Black should be fine. }
13. Qf3
{ A very critical line. Black must know exactly what to do here.   13.g4  ,  13.Nd5  ,  13.Kb1  and the dangerous  13.Rxd7!?  are White's alternative analyzed in chapter 5. }
13... Bg7
{ Now the bishop comes to g7. If  13...Be7?  White wins after  14.Rxd7! } 14.
a3 O-O 15. Kb1 Bb7 16. g4 Rab8 { The only good plan for Black. } 17. g5 hxg5
18. Bxg5 { Now Black has a very good continuation. } 18... Rfc8
{ Threatening ...Ne4 or even ...Be4. } 19. Bd3 a5
{ Black is fully ready for this push. The position is very concrete. I think White also should be very careful here, as the pawn on e4 is hanging in many lines. For example after  20.Nxb5  Black continues with  20...Bxe4  , or after @@StartFEN@@1rr3k1/1bqn1pb1/5np1/pp2p1B1/4P3/PNNB1Q2/1PP4P/1K1R3R w - - 0 20@@EndFEN@@  20.Bxb5  Nxe4  . }
