10... Nbd7 11. a4 { 11.Nd5  again transposesto 8.Be3 Be6 9.Nd5. } 11... Rc8
{ Black should start with this move. Worse is  11...Nb6?!  12.Nd2!  ,  which is the point of 10. Qd3. }
12. a5 Qc7 13. Rfd1 Rfd8 { The most logical place for the rook. } 14. Bf3 Nc5
{ The most concrete way to equalize. } 15. Nxc5 { The theoretical move. } 15...
dxc5 16. Nd5
{ Harmless is  16.Qe2  Rxd1+  The simplest way to equalize.  17.Qxd1  Rd8  18.Qe1  h6= }
16... Nxd5 17. exd5 f5 { The point! With this move Black equalizes. } 18. Qb3
Bf7 19. c4 e4 { Black starts counter-attacking. } 20. Be2 f4 21. Bd2 Rf8
{ Black had fantastic attacking chances in the game: Hovhannisyan,R @@StartBracket@@2642@@EndBracket@@-Ter Sahakyan,S  @@StartBracket@@2640@@EndBracket@@ Yerevan 2021. }
