1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+
{ The most popular way to deviate from the Open Sicilian. This system is quite unpleasant for Black because it is very solid and it is quite difficult to gain any activity. Nevertheless, Black has several options to have an equal game. }
3... Bd7
{ The most solid approach. Both  3...Bd7  and  3...Nd7  are the most popular move. Lately the move  3...Nc6  is considered to be a little worse for Black. }
4. Bxd7+ { In addition to this move, White has several other alternatives. }
4... Qxd7 5. c4
{ The main setup.  5.O-O  , the other main move, can be found starting from here. }
5... e5
{ A rare move that has become very popular in recent years due to World Champion Magnus Carlsen. It may be a little passive, but very solid and the plans are very clear. The main idea of course is to close the center and not give White a chance to play d4. Then the main plan is to play ...Be7-d8, ...Nge7 and to push f5 at the right moment.   The main moves are  5...Nf6  and  5...Nc6  . }
6. Nc3 Nc6 7. d3
{ It makes sense to postpone castling because White's idea is after  7...g6  to play  8.h4! }
7... Be7
{ The best plan in this position and the favourite plan of the Champ Magnus. Black's next moves are very easy. }
8. a3 Bd8 { The point of Black's idea. } 9. O-O Nge7 10. b4 O-O
{ 10...cxb4?!  This is not Black's idea.  11.axb4  Nxb4  12.Ba3  Nbc6  13.d4  . }
11. bxc5
{ 11.Rb1  is also possible, but it brings nothing special.  11...f5  Black continues with his plan.  12.exf5  Nxf5=  The chances are equal. }
11... dxc5 12. Nd5 Ng6
{ Prepares f5 at the right moment. Also fine is immediately  12...f5!? } 13.
Be3 b6 14. Nd2 f5
{ Black has enough counterplay in the game: Kovalev,V @@StartBracket@@2661@@EndBracket@@ - Carlsen,M @@StartBracket@@2876@@EndBracket@@, Douglas 2019. }
