7... g6 8. Qf3 Qxg5 9. Bxd5 { Now ...Qf6 is not possible. } 9... Nd8
{ The only move to protect everything. } 10. O-O Qe7
{ The threat was d4. Now Black just wants to develop his pieces. Worse is  10...Qf5?!  11.Qe3  . }
11. d4 { The most direct. } 11... cxd4 12. cxd4 exd4 13. b3
{ A very creative idea, but with accurate play, Black can defend. The alternative  13.Bf4  can be found starting from here. }
13... Be6 14. Nd2
{ If  14.Ba3?!  then  14...Qg5  15.Bxe6  fxe6  Black remains a pawn up and is slightly better. }
14... Bh6 { It is a good idea to exchange the bishop on c1. } 15. Ne4 Bxc1 16.
Raxc1 O-O { Black has no problems. } *

