8. Be3 e6 9. Bg2 Qc7 { Black is good after: } 10. f4 b5 11. e5 Bb7
{ It is very important that the bishop on g2 is not yet protected. } 12. exd6
Bxd6 13. Bxb7 Qxb7 14. Qf3 Rb8
{ With a slightly more comfortable endgame for Black. An interesting idea can be to play ...Bb4 next. }
