8... Be7 9. Kh1 { White prepares f4. } 9... O-O 10. f4
{ This is not good right away because of Black's  10...h6! } 10... h6 11. Bh4
Nxe4 { Once again this typical trick! } 12. Bxe7 Nxc3 13. Bxd8 Nxd1
{ With a clear pawn up for Black. } *

