{ White's best sideline on move 7. White wants to prevent b5 and then continue with Be2, O-O and possibly f4. There are some top players who have tried this move, which means it deserves serious attention. }
7... e6 8. Bd3
{ The bishop on d3 is almost never great due to the possibility of Black playing ...Ne5. }
8... Be7 9. O-O O-O 10. a5 Ne5
{ Black threatens to play once again the typical ...b5 break. } 11. f4 Nxd3 12.
Qxd3 h6 { It is always good to include ...h6 in these positions. } 13. Bh4 Qc7
14. Kh1 Bd7
{ Already I slightly prefer Black. White has no attack, and with the bishop pair Black has excellent chances to be better in the long term. }
