8. Bxf6 { A solid but not very ambitious line. } 8... Nxf6 9. O-O-O
{ 9.f4?!  e5!  is just bad for White. } 9... e5
{ The most natural move. I believe that the Black's next moves are quite easy. }
10. Nf5 g6 11. Ne3 Be6
{ Black's next moves are ...Rc8 and ...h5/...Bh6, bringing the bishop to the h6-c1 diagonal from where it will be very active. }
12. g3
{ White must somehow develop his bishop.   12.Ned5  does not change much.  12...Nxd5  13.Nxd5  Rc8  14.Kb1  Rc5=  The threat is to exchange on d5. }
12... Rc8 { Creating the possibility of ...Rxc3 in some positions. } 13. Rd3
{ Protecting the knight on c3 for the moment. } 13... h5
{ The idea is to bring the bishop to a more active position on h6. } 14. Bg2
Bh6 15. Kb1 Qa5 { Again with the threat of ...Rxc3. } 16. a3
{ Another normal reply to consider. } 16... O-O 17. Rhd1 Kg7
{ A nice prophylactic move. } 18. Rxd6
{ This move always will be met by the exchange sacrifice on c3. } 18... Rxc3
19. bxc3 Rc8 { White has too many weaknesses. } *

