10. Nb3
{ In some recent games White has tried to play f4 anyway, but after  9...e5  10.f4  exd4  11.e5  dxc3  12.exf6+  Ne5  13.fxe5  Be6  Black has a decisive advantage. }
10... Be7
{ The bishop is no longer necessary on g7. From e7 it will protect the d6-pawn. Another plan in this position is ...Kf8-g7. }
11. f3
{ This is the most played move, but I believe that Black has good counter-chances. }
11... b5 12. a3 { It seems normal to stop ...b4. } 12... Kf8
{ I have already mentioned that this plan is very important. } 13. Kb1 Kg7 14.
Nc1 { Looks nice, but is a bit slow. } 14... Nb6 15. N1a2 Be6 16. Nb4 Rc8
{ Black creates threats very quickly. ...a6-a5 is an unpleasant threat. } *

