{ Black must repeat moves after  21.Kc1  Qa1+=  . } 21... Rxb4
{ The best way to continue the initiative. } 22. cxb4
{ White is losing easily after  22.Qxc8+?  Ke7  23.d6+  Ke6  White is getting mated soon.   22.Qxb4  This looks dangerous for White.  22...Qxb4  23.cxb4  e4  Black has excellent compensation for the exchange. Black's bishops are very strong. }
22... O-O 23. Bd3 Nb6 24. Qc5
{ Here Black has several different ways to make a draw. } 24... Nd7 25. Qc4
{ 25.Qa5  is dangerous only for White.  25...Qb3  26.Bc2  Qc4  27.Kc1  Qg4  After e5-e4 Black's bishop on g7 will be extremely strong. }
25... Nb6 { White must repeat the moves. } *

