{ Quite a popular move. The idea is after  10...Nc6  to play  11.Nb3  . } 10...
Nc6 { The only logical move. } 11. Nb3
{ In case of  11.Nxc6  bxc6  Black is at least not worse. } 11... b5
{ The best move. } 12. h4
{ The most critical line. The other moves are less dangerous for Black. For example, after  12.O-O-O  Black continues with  12...Nge5  a very standard move. The knight goes to c4. }
12... gxh4
{ I prefer this move.  12...b4  13.Nd5  is interesting but very risky for Black. }
13. Bxh4 Nge5 { Black relocates the knight, now useless in g4. } 14. Nd5 Nc4
15. Bxc4 bxc4 16. Nc1 Rb8
{ I think it is a good idea to start with this move. Unclear is  16...Be6  , Giri @@StartBracket@@2755@@EndBracket@@ - Gelfand @@StartBracket@@2743@@EndBracket@@, Moscow 2016. }
17. Rb1 { For the moment White protects the b2-pawn. } 17... f5
{ Opening up the position. } 18. exf5 Bxf5 19. O-O Qa5
{ Black aims for an endgame. } 20. b4 { White must play this move! } 20... cxb3
21. Qxa5 Nxa5 22. Nxb3 Nc6
{ The endgame is very playable. The bishop pair gives Black a lot of chances. }
