11... Nc6 { Black must start with this move. } 12. Nxc6 bxc6 13. e5
{ The point behind 11. Qe2. } 13... dxe5 14. Bxe5 O-O
{ The critical position. } 15. g4
{ A very aggressive way of playing. The point is to play h4 next. } 15... a5
{ The same as in the 15. g3 variation. } 16. h4
{ This position arose in the game Dominguez Perez,L @@StartBracket@@2717@@EndBracket@@-Karjakin,S @@StartBracket@@2706@@EndBracket@@ Wijk aan Zee 2009. }
16... a4
{ Black does not care about the g4-pawn. ...Ra5 is now a very important threat. }
17. hxg5 hxg5 18. Qe3 { Preparing Qh3. } 18... Nxg4 19. Qh3 Nh6
{ A nice defense! Black has very good chances to defend successfully. } *

