{ We've arrived at the critical position for the whole 10... Nf6 line. White has a couple of interesting ideas in this position. }
18. b3
{ Another option to consider is  18.Bd3  Bb7  19.Qd4  when we have  19...h5  with the threat of ...Qa5. }
18... Bb7 19. Qd2 { Black has many decent ideas here. } 19... dxe5
{ Not the only move, but I like it a lot. } 20. Qc3 Rc8
{ An important intermediate move. } 21. Bc4 Rxc4
{ The point behind 19... dxe5. } 22. bxc4
{ Dangerous for White is  22.Qxc4  Qa5!  when Black's attacking chances are very serious. }
22... Qc7 23. Rhe1 f6
{ The White's bishop is completely neutralized. The compensation for the exchange is clear. }
*

