11. c3 Be7 { Here this is the best move. Now White must stop ...Bh4+. } 12. h4
{ It is necessary to prevent the check on h4. } 12... Nc6 13. Nb3 f5
{ A bit of a weird move, but it also creates some weaknesses in White's camp. }
14. Be2 fxg4 { The logical continuation of the previous move. } 15. Qxd5 exd5
16. fxg4 Ne5 { Black has equal chances in the endgame. } *

