1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. f3
{ This is the other way for White to play the English Attack. White skips the  6.Be3  Ng4  line. The main difference is that now after  6.f3  , Black can choose the system with  6...e6  , which has always been my favorite reply.   The difference with  6.Be3  e6  is that there White has a very attractive idea which is  7.Be2  with the same plan to play Qd2 or even g4 in some lines. Honestly, I think Black's position is quite suspect in that variation. }
6... e6 7. g4
