8. Be3 { 8.h4  d5!  is an even better version for Black than 8. Be3 d5. } 8...
d5
{ I believe this is the best move here.   8...b5  9.a3!  Now Black has no ideas with ...h5.  9...Bb7  10.Qd2   @@StartBracket@@  10.h4!?  is also very interesting.@@EndBracket@@  10...Nbd7  11.O-O-O  Rc8  This is a very well-known theoretical position, where Black has some problems. For example  12.h4  d5  13.Rg1  dxe4  14.g5  hxg5  15.hxg5  Nd5  16.Nxd5  Bxd5  17.fxe4  Bxe4  18.Bg2  .   After  8...d5  we arrive at a completely new position. White now has two critical options. }
9. e5 { The most natural. } 9... Nfd7 10. f4 Qb6
{ Clearly the best move.   After  10...Nc6?!  the position is very dangerous for Black:  11.Qd2!  Qh4+  12.Bf2  Nxd4  13.Qxd4  Qxg4  14.Rg1  Qh5  15.h4  Bc5  16.Qd2  . }
11. a3
{ Defending the b2-pawn. Of course the idea is after  11...Qxb2  to win the queen with  12.Na4!  +-   After  11.Na4  Qa5+  12.Nc3  Black can simply repeat moves with  12...Qb6=  . }
11... Nc6 12. Nf5 { The most interesting try. } 12... Qc7
{ Black must play solidly for now. } 13. Bg2
{ White wants to castle short and put more pressure on the d5-pawn.   After  13.Qd2  b5!  Black will create counterplay very quickly with ...b4. }
13... b5
{ The position looks very attractive to White, but I think Black has decent chances.   Black can't really touch the knight on f5 as it would lead to a lost position after  13...exf5  14.Nxd5  Qd8  15.Qe2  Be7  16.O-O-O  O-O  17.gxf5 }
14. Bxd5 { The most direct approach. } 14... exf5 15. gxf5 Bb7
{ The position looks very tricky for both sides. Black definitely has his chances. }
16. Bxf7+ { Tempting, but it just leads to a draw. } 16... Kxf7 17. Nd5 Qa5+
{ It's very important to include this check! } 18. b4 Qd8 19. e6+ Kg8
{ The only good aquare for the king. } 20. exd7
{ White has regained one of the pieces, but now it's Black's turn to counter-attack. }
20... Qh4+ 21. Bf2 Qh3 { White's king is in trouble now. } 22. Nf6+
{ Forcing the draw. } 22... gxf6 23. Qd5+ Kh7 24. Qf7+ Bg7 25. Qg6+ Kg8
{ White must take the draw with  26.Qe8+  Kh7  27.Qg6+  Kg8=  . } *

