[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "13) 6.f3 e6 7.Be3 Minor Lines"]
[Black "6.f3 e6 7.Be3 with 8.a3 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. f3 e6 7. Be3
{ The most popular move is also the most logical for White. } 7... b5
{ Black has some alternatives, but this is the most natural move in the Najdorf. }
8. a3 { An interesting idea. For now White wants to prevent ...b4. } 8... h5
{ Now Black has the chance to stop g2-g4. With the moves ...b5 and a3 included, this is clearly the best way to play. The point is that White has already committed with a3, so it's not possible to play a2-a4. }
9. Be2 { White can try to play with short castle. } 9... Nbd7 10. a4
{ If White attacks the b-pawn, Black must respond by advancing. } 10... b4 11.
Nc6 Qc7 12. Nxb4 d5 { Black takes the initiative. } *

