[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. f3 e6 7. Be3
{ The most popular move is also the most logical for White. } 7... b5
{ Black has some alternatives, but this is the most natural move in the Najdorf. }
8. Qd2 { The most popular and probably the best move. } 8... Nbd7
{ The most flexible move. The other main line is  8...Bb7  .   8...h5?!  here is not a good idea because of  9.a4!  b4  10.Na2  and White is better.   Another popular line is  8...b4  9.Na4  Nbd7  . The latest games suggest that  10.Bc4!?  is very promising for White, for instance  10...Ne5  11.Bb3  . }
9. a3 h5
{ We have already seen that against 8. a3 Black plays ...h5! After the move a3, advancing ...h5 is usually a very good idea, and here it works as well. }
10. a4
{ Now Black is ready for this move.   10.O-O-O  Bb7  transposes to the main line 9.O-O-O. }
10... b4 11. Na2 d5 { White is just not ready in the center. } 12. Nxb4 dxe4
13. Nbc6 Qc7 { Black is clearly better. } *

