{ 6.h3  is one of the most popular systems against the Najdorf nowadays. The main idea is to push g4 as soon as possible. }
6... Nc6
{ This is not the most popular response from Black. The main moves are  6...e5  and  6...e6  .  6...g6  is also an option, very similar to the move I'm offering.I decided to suggest  6...Nc6  because I think it leads to very playable positions and is also a bit rare compared to the other moves just mentioned, where the theory is huge. The main idea is to play with ...g6 and ...Bg7 next, but as we will see, against some moves Black will play with ...e5 instead. }
7. g4 { The main move, and the most logical follow up after h3. } 7... g6
{ The point of Black's previous move. } 8. Be3
{ Usually White plays these positions with the intention to castle long, and in that sense it's better to start with Be3. }
8... Nxd4
{ A very important move order. Black must start with this move! This line become very popular after the game Karjakin-Shankland in the Fide World Cup 2021. }
9. Qxd4 { The most critical move. } 9... Bg7
{ The critical position. Now White has a few different ways of playing. } 10.
Qb4 { Also very tempting. It threatens Bb6. } 10... O-O
{ Black has nothing better than just castling. } 11. Bb6 Qe8 12. O-O-O Be6
{ Black must develop some pieces. } 13. f4 Qc6 14. Bd4 Rfc8
{ The position is very complicated. Definitely Black has his chances. } *

