7. g4 { The main move, and the most logical follow up after h3. } 7... g6
{ The point of Black's previous move. } 8. Be3
{ Usually White plays these positions with the intention to castle long, and in that sense it's better to start with Be3. }
8... Nxd4
{ A very important move order. Black must start with this move! This line become very popular after the game Karjakin-Shankland in the Fide World Cup 2021. }
9. Qxd4 { The most critical move. } 9... Bg7
{ The critical position. Now White has a few different ways of playing. } 10.
O-O-O { The most natural continuation. } 10... O-O 11. Qb4
{ Played recently by Alireza Firouzja. } 11... Nd7
{ A very important improvement!   11...a5  was played in Firouzja - Saric, Terme Catez 2021. The best move here was  12.Qb6!  Qxb6  13.Bxb6  Be6  14.f4  Nd7  15.Bd4  With an endgame that's more comfortable for White. }
12. Nd5 { A standard move. } 12... b5 13. Bd4 Bxd4 14. Qxd4 Bb7
{ Black has very good counterplay. Here, in contrast tothe following line,  15.h4  leads nowhere because of  15...e5  16.Qd2  Bxd5  17.Qxd5  Nf6!  when Black can take over easily. }
*

