1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be2
{ One of the most popular systems against the Najdorf, considered to be the most positional approach.  Many great players have had this move as their main weapon against the Najdorf. }
6... e5
{ The main move.  6...e6  would lead to Scheveningen type of positions.  6...e5  is the most popular move these days, and almost all top players prefer it. }
7. Nf5 { This is not a good idea, because of Black's reaction in the centre. }
7... d5 { White is already slightly worse and should be very careful. } 8. Bg5
d4 9. Bxf6 Qxf6 { The simplest. } 10. Nd5 Qd8 11. Bc4 Nc6
{ Black has an easy plan: ...Be6 and then ...g6. } 12. O-O Be6 13. c3 g6 14.
Ng3 Rc8 { Black has a fantastic position. } *

