1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be2
{ One of the most popular systems against the Najdorf, considered to be the most positional approach.  Many great players have had this move as their main weapon against the Najdorf. }
6... e5
{ The main move.  6...e6  would lead to Scheveningen type of positions.  6...e5  is the most popular move these days, and almost all top players prefer it. }
7. Nf3
{ Since Magnus Carlsen played it, this move has become very popular in recent years.  The main idea is to play Bg5-Bxf6 with the intention of taking control of the d5-square. }
7... Be7 { The main move. } 8. O-O
{ This is not a logical continuation of White's previous move. } 8... Be6
{ Now Black is ready to continue, after  9.Bg5  , with  9...Nbd7  . } 9. Ng5
Bd7 10. Bc4 { Black can simply castle. } 10... O-O
{ White's knight will soon have to retreat from g5. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
