{ A rare move, but Black should definitely know what to do here. } 11... Bxd5
12. exd5 Nb6
{ I like to start with this move instead of ...Rc8, because now it's mandatory for White to play Bf3. }
13. Bf3 Nfd7 { Black has a very direct plan now: ...f5 and ...e4. } 14. h4
{ After  14.g4  strong is  14...Bg5!  15.h4  Bxe3+  16.fxe3  Na4!  when I like Black's chances. }
14... f5 15. Be2 Na4
{ Despite being on the rim, a4 is a very good outpost for the knight. The pawn on b2 can be attacked in the future. }
16. Kb1 b5 17. c3 Ndb6 { Black has a strong initiative. } *

