{ The old move. Nowadays more popular is Grischuk's choice  13...Ne8  . The point behind move  13...a5  is that for the moment Black wants to stop all of White's ideas on the queenside and only then start active operations in the centre or on the kingside. }
14. Kh1
{ A very normal prophylactic move. White is preparing f2-f4 and will also decide later where to place the rook from a1.White has many different ideas here. A popular plan is to prepare f4 with Rae1 or first Kh1. Another plan is to bring the rook from a1 to the center either c1 or d1 and then try to transfer the knight from b3 to b5 via d2-b1-c3. }
14... g6 { The other possible moves are  14...b6  or even  14...h5  . } 15.
Rae1 { White continues to prepare f2-f4. } 15... Re8 { A decent waiting move. }
16. f4 { Black is ready for this push. } 16... a4
{ Once again, attacking the knight before taking on f4. } 17. Nd2 exf4 18. Bxf4
Bf8 { ...Ne5 will come next. } *

