10... O-O 11. O-O Bxd5 { This move is practically forced. } 12. exd5
{ A very critical position for the theory. The struggle is very positional. Mostly White focuses on pushing pawns on the queenside, and Black is trying to play on the kingside. Black has plenty of different plans, though. }
12... Rc8
{ Recently, Black has more often tried  12...Ne8  . Another very popular move is  12...Nc5  , but the position after  13.Nxc5  dxc5  14.Bf3  is not my favorite. I believe White has some plus here.   Another critical option is  12...h5!?  which definitely is very interesting. }
13. c4
{ The main move.   13.a4?!  The point of Black's previous move is shown by  13...Nb6!  when White needs to exchange on b6, giving Black an excellent position.   13.Rac1  After this move, Black can already play  13...h5  ,  with a better version of 12... h5. }
