14... g6 { The other possible moves are  14...b6  or even  14...h5  . } 15.
Rae1 { White continues to prepare f2-f4. } 15... Re8 { A decent waiting move. }
16. f3 { It's hard for White to just wait like this. } 16... Nh5
{ Now Black gets very nice counterplay. } 17. g3 Bg5 18. Bg1 Nhf6
{ Preparing ...e5-e4. } 19. Nd2 e4 { A very typical pawn sacrifice. } 20. Nxe4
{ Or  20.fxe4  Nc5  21.Bxc5  Rxc5  and Black has excellent control over the dark squares. }
20... Nxe4 21. fxe4 Qe7
{ Black equalizes easily. White will not be able to defend both the c4- and e4-pawns. }
