{ Practice has shown that this is the best move order. If Black starts with  7...Be6  , then White can play  8.f4  with the idea of ​​disturbing the bishop with f4-f5. }
8. O-O O-O 9. Kh1
{ One of the most popular moves. The idea is to wait for  9...Be6  and just then to push  10.f4  . }
9... Re8
{ An extremely rare idea. I'd like to suggest this move because there is much less theory, it has not been studied as the other moves, but on the other hand it gives Black equal chances. White has many possible replies, and it is difficult to decide which is the best try.   Black's main moves are  9...Nc6  and  9...b6  . }
10. f4
{ This is a bit strange, because it is obvious that ...Re8 is directed against this move. }
10... Nc6 { The most natural reply. } 11. Be3
{ Of course now Black will already take on f4. } 11... exf4
{ Black is ready to open files. } 12. Rxf4 Be6 13. Nd5 Nd7
{ Threatening ...Bg5. } 14. Nxe7+ Qxe7 15. Nd4 Nce5
{ Black has a very stable position. } *

