{ In this particular line the knight always goes to c6! } 12. Kb1
{ Probably the best move order. Black has a couple of good ideas now. } 12...
Nxd4 { This move is the one I like the most. } 13. Bxd4
{ An inaccuracy is  13.Qxd4?!  Bc6!  preparing ...a5. Black's attack will be faster. }
13... Bc6
{ An interesting idea inspired by the game Svidler-Kasparov from a completely different line in the Sicilan. }
14. Bxf6 Bxf6 15. Qxd6 Qxd6 16. Rxd6 Rfc8
{ The bishop pair, the dark-squared one being particularly strong, gives Black enough compensation for the pawn. }
