{ This move has been popular lately. The idea is to provoke b7-b5 and to avoid the lines with ...Nbd7. }
7... b5 { I believe Black must start with this move. } 8. Bb3 Be7
{ The most accurate move order. The point is to still keep the pawn on e6 protected. Also, in some lines the bishop can go to d7. }
9. a3 { Probably the best move order. White is preventing ...b4. } 9... O-O 10.
f3 Bb7 11. Qe2 Nc6 { The move I like the most. } 12. O-O-O b4
