{ The modern line, played by Vladimir Kramnik. It is very similar to the line with 7. Be3, the main difference being that Black's knight is already on d7. }
8... Nc5 9. f3 Be7
{ I prefer to play this way, although other moves are also very possible. The point is that Black can continue with ... Bd7 and ...b5 next. }
10. Qd2 Bd7 11. g4
{ This is better than castling.   After  11.O-O-O?!  b5  Black's plan is to push ...b4 or play ...Qb8 first and then ...a5 and ...b4. It seems very difficult for White to stop this attack. }
11... b5 12. a3
{ In case of  12.g5  Nh5  the knight stops all of White's attacking chances. }
12... Rb8 { Black has a fantastic position. } *

