{ The knight looks very good here. } 12. Re1
{ The point is after  12.Be3  to continue with  12...Ng4!  Attacking the knight on h4 is very unpleasant for White. }
12... g6 { Stopping Nf5. } 13. Bh6 Re8 14. Nf3 Nxf3+ 15. Qxf3 Rc8
{ Black has no problems at all. ...Qb6 can be an interesting idea for Black. }
