{ I prefer to develop and castle for now. The alternatives are  7...b5  and  7...Nbd7  . }
8. Bg2 O-O { The other option is  8...b5  . } 9. O-O b5
{ The main move.  9...Be6  is the other line, but theory has shown that Black is slightly worse after  10.a4  Nbd7  11.h3  . }
10. a4
{ The main try is  10.Nd5  , but Black is doing fine after  10.a4  as well. }
10... b4 11. Nd5 Nxd5 12. Qxd5 Qc7 { Leaving the rook unprotected. } 13. Qxa8
Nc6
{ This is the difference between the immediate 10. Nd5 and including the moves 10. a4 b4 first. The point is that in this position White can no longer play the move Nc3! Black will play ...Bb7 next with a clear advantage. }
*

