[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. a3
{ A rare line played a lot by the World Champion Magnus Carlsen. This is a waiting move. The main idea is after  6...e5  7.Nf5  d5  to play  8.Bg5  ,  and in many lines the pawn on a3 protects against the possible check on b4. }
6... e5 { I think this is the best reaction to 6. a3. } 7. Nf5
{ The main idea of White's previous move. The alternatives are less ambitious. For example,  7.Nb3  is a possible move, but not very well connected to 6. a3. Black will simply develop with  7...Be6  . The move 6. a3 here is just a lost of time. }
7... d5
{ Worse is  7...Bxf5?!  8.exf5  d5  bacause of  9.Bg5  d4  10.Ne4  The point of 6. a3. Now Black doesn't have the move ...Bb4+. }
8. Bg5 d4 9. Bxf6 gxf6
{ The most ambitious continuation. The main point is that Nd5 is not possible because the knight on f5 is hanging.   The other way to play is  9...Qxf6  10.Nd5  Qc6  . }
10. Nb1 { White wants to occupy the light squares with Bd3 and Qh5. } 10...
Bxf5 { A bit risky positionally, but it works very well. } 11. exf5 Qd5
{ Intending ...Nd7. The queen is very well placed on d5 for now. } 12. Qh5 Nd7
{ Black simply wants to develop. Unclear is  12...Qe4+  13.Kd1  . } 13. Nd2
O-O-O { I prefer to put my king to safety. } 14. Qf3
{ White must play safely now. In case of  14.Bd3  Qxg2  15.Be4  Black should continue  15...Qg5  16.Qf3  Nc5  with very strong counterplay. }
14... Qa5
{ I like this improvement. The endgame after  14...Qxf3  15.gxf3  is very safe for Black, but White was also out of danger in Kramer, J. - Cheparinov, I., Tornelo INT 2021. }
15. Kd1
{ The king is kind of safe here.   15.O-O-O  is terrible because of  15...Bh6  when Black is better as this pin is very nasty. }
15... e4 { A thematic idea. Black opens more files against the white king. }
16. Qxe4 Ne5 { Black has a nice initiative. } 17. Bd3 { Not a good idea. }
17... Bh6
{ With ...Rhe8 next. Black's dark-squared bishop is very active on that diagonal. }
*

