1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. a4
{ This is a very positional line. It should be clear that White intends to play with short castling. }
6... e5 { Here again, I prefer to play with the e7-e5 plan. } 7. Nb3 Be6
{ Black will develop in the usual way. } 8. f4 Nc6
{ Now the knight is better placed on c6. Black intends to continue with ...Nd4 after exchanging White's b3-knight. }
9. f5 Bxb3 10. cxb3 d5 { This is the point! } 11. exd5 Nd4 12. Bd3 Bc5
{ Black is better as White cannot castle. } *

