1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Qd3
{ This queen move became very popular a few years ago. Usually moving the queen this early is not a good idea, but with the new and much more powerful engines anything is possible.   6.Qd3  is actually very interesting. The main point is that now  6...e5  is dubious in view of  7.Nf5  Bxf5  8.exf5  d5  9.Bg5⩲  . }
6... g6
{ To play the Dragon against the queen on d3 seems like a logical idea. Many other moves are quite possible as well. For example:  6...e6  ,  6...Nbd7  or  6...Nc6  . }
7. f3 { White tries to skip the line  7.Be3  Ng4  . } 7... b5 { The best! } 8.
Be3 Bb7 9. a4
{ The only critical try. After  9.O-O-O  Nbd7  the queen on d3 is a little awkward. }
9... b4 10. Na2 e5
{ Black will play d6-d5 next and will completely crush the center. } 11. Nb3 d5
{ The position becomes very concrete. Black is doing very well. } *

