12... Bxe5 { The only move. } 13. Nc7+ Kd7
{ The key move here! The point of 12.e5 is that after  13...Kf8?  White has the idea  14.Nde6+!  Bxe6  15.Qxe5!  dxe5  16.Nxe6+  fxe6  17.Rxd8+  Kg7  18.Rxh8  Kxh8  19.Bc4  with a big advantage in the endgame. }
14. Nd5 e6 { Perhaps the easiest way to deal with this position. } 15. f4 Bg7
{ Of course for now Black is keeping his strong bishop alive. } 16. Nxe6
{ The only move. } 16... Bxc3 17. Nxd8 Bxb2+ 18. Kxb2 Kxd8
{ White will probably be able to make a draw, but Black is not in danger at all. }
