{ A very important improvement! Much worse is  11...Nd7?  12.Bxf4  Nce5?   Better is  12...h6  13.Rf1+=  13.Qd2  b5  14.O-O-O  Rakotomaharo, F @@StartBracket@@2429@@EndBracket@@ - Perez Ponsa, F @@StartBracket@@2554@@EndBracket@@, chess.com 2021. }
12. Bxf3 Nd7 13. Bf4 h6
{ It is very important to create counterplay very quickly. } 14. Qd2 Nce5
{ The square e5 is just great for Black's knights. } 15. Be2 hxg5
{ The next few moves are forced. } 16. Bxg5 Be7 17. Bxe7 Qxe7 18. O-O-O O-O-O
{ There is no way to defend the d6 pawn. } 19. Qxd6 Qxd6 20. Rxd6
{ Black is not worse, despite being a pawn down. } 20... Rde8
{ One of the good moves. } 21. Nd5 Kb8
{ The weak pawn on h4 gives Black a very nice compensation. } *

