1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. b3
{ Another modern move, played recently by David Navara. At least this move has a clear idea, which is to fianchetto the bishop and then to continue with Qd2 and O-O-O. }
6... e5 { Any other move should be also good. } 7. Nde2 Be6
{ With the idea of ...d5 in some lines. There are so many good move here, such as  7...Nc6  ,  7...Be7  or  7...Nbd7  . All of them are very playable. }
8. g3 d5 { Not mandatory at all, but why not? } 9. exd5 Nxd5 10. Bg2 Bb4
{ This move is very important. The pin gives Black an important tempo to play ...Nc6 next. }
11. Bb2 Nc6 12. O-O Nf6
{ It seems like it's a good idea not to trade minor pieces for the time being. }
13. Qxd8+ Rxd8 14. Rad1 O-O { The endgame should be very drawish. } *

