[Black "6.Bd2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bd2
{ One of the most ridiculous moves I've ever seen. I don't see the point in this move, to be honest. I decided to analyze it and it is now in the course only because it was played by a strong and respected Grandmaster. }
6... e5 { The most logical response in my view. } 7. Nf5 d5
{ I like this aproach! Is similar to the 6.a3 line. } 8. Qf3
{ White has no other options here. } 8... d4 9. Nd5 Nxd5 10. exd5 Bxf5
{ The simplest. } 11. Qxf5 Nd7 { Black is doing fantastic. } 12. O-O-O g6
{ The bishop will be better on g7. } 13. Qf3 Bg7
{ Black wants to castle next. } 14. Bb4
{ Trying to keep the king in the central squares. } 14... Qb6 15. Ba3 Bf8
{ Black has the better chances. } *

