{ It is important to start with this move. White needs to defend his pawn now. }
10. Nf5
{ The other moves are absolutely harmless. For example  10.Bc4  g6!  Already very good.  11.b3  Bg7  12.Bb2  O-O  13.Qe2  Nd7  and Black has fantastic counter-chances. }
10... Qc7 { The most accurate move order. } 11. Qg4
{ Provoking g6 makes sense. } 11... g6 12. Qd4
{ After  12.Ne3  the simple  12...Bg7  13.Qxb4  O-O  is good enough. } 12...
Rg8 13. Ne3 Qc5 { The endgame looks equal. } 14. Qxc5
{ Black equalizes easily. } 14... dxc5 15. g3 Nd7 16. Bg2 Bg7
{ Black has no problems. } *

