{ Not the most popular, but definitely the most ambitious move. It complicates the game and gives Black an excellent chance to fight for an advantage.   The most popular move is  7...Be6  . }
8. c3 { White must exchange this very strong central pawn on d4. } 8... Nc6
{ White has two main options here,  9.cxd4  and  9.Bb5  . } 9. cxd4
{ Definitely the most critical. In all other lines, White risks being worse. }
9... Bb4+
{ A very important intermediate check. Worse is  9...exd4?!  10.Bb5  . } 10.
Bd2 { The only serious try. } 10... O-O
{ A very interesting novelty. Risky, but even White should know what to do.   The theoretical move is  10...Nxe4!?  11.Bxb4  Qh4+  12.g3  Nxg3  13.hxg3  Qxh1  . }
11. Bxb4 { The critical line. } 11... Nxb4 12. Qd2 Nxe4
{ Once again this tactic! } 13. Qxb4 { It is worse than  13.fxe4  . } 13... a5
14. Qc4 Qh4+ 15. g3 Nxg3 16. hxg3 Qxh1 { Black is better. } *

