{ The best square. Now the d6-pawn is very well protected. } 12. Ng5 Nxe5 13.
Nxe6 fxe6 14. f4
{ Worse is  14.Qxa7?!  in view of  14...d5!  15.Qxb7  Nd6  Black has a serious initiative. }
14... Bh6 { The whole point! } 15. Rf1 Ng7
{ Protects the pawn on e6 and also threatens ...Nf5 in some lines. } 16. Qxa7
Nc4 17. Qxb7 Nf5 { Black has a fantastic compensation for the pawn. } *

