5... Nc6 6. Bb5 Bd7 7. Bxc6 Bxc6
{ White already committed with Nc3 and the plan c4-Nc3 is not possible now. This line was very popular in the past. Nowadays Black is happy to reach this position. }
8. Bg5 e6 9. O-O-O
{ 9.Bxf6  Qxf6  10.Qxf6  gxf6=  The endgame is very good for Black. } 9... Be7
{ White has many different options. The most popular lately is  10.Qd3  . } 10.
Qd3
{ White wants to continue with Nd4. If White wants to play for a draw, the best continuation is  10.Bxf6  Bxf6  11.Qxd6  Qxd6  12.Rxd6  Bxc3  13.bxc3  Bxe4=  After all these forced moves, the endgame appears very much equal. }
10... h6 { I prefer to start with this move before castling. } 11. Bh4 O-O 12.
Nd4 Qc7 { A good place for Black's queen. } 13. Rhe1
{ In case of  13.f4  possible is  13...Nxe4!?  A typical tactic. Here it leads only to equality.  14.Ncb5  Qd8  15.Nxc6  bxc6  16.Nxd6  Nc5  One of the possible moves.  17.Qc3  Bxh4  18.Qxc5  Qb6  19.Qxb6  axb6=  The endgame is very level. }
