15. Bxf6 Bxf6 16. Qxd6 Qb6
{ It seems that keeping the queens is good for now. } 17. Qg3 Rab8
{ White's position is quite dangerous. } 18. b3 c5 19. e5 Bg5+
{ It is very important to include this check before retreating the bishop. After  19...Bg5+  20.f4  Be7  21.Rd7  c4  22.Rxe7  cxb3  23.axb3  Qb4  Black will take back the piece and the position is equal.   But after  19...Be7  20.Rd7  c4  21.Rxe7  cxb3  22.Qf3  White is attacking  f7  , with a completely won position. }
20. f4 Be7 { Black has very good compensation for the pawn. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
