1. e4 c5 2. c3
{ The Alapin has always bothered me a lot. It is very difficult for Black to create fighting opportunities. }
2... e5
{ The line that I suggest is extremely rare compared to  2...d5  and  2...Nf6  . I think is nice to have this line in our repertoire, because is less known and objectively Black is fine as well. }
3. Nf3 Nc6 4. Bb5 { Is almost the Spanish Opening. } 4... a6
{ Not the most common, but definitely the most logical move. } 5. Bxc6
{ Harmless. } 5... dxc6 6. O-O
{ If  6.Nxe5?!  then  6...Qg5  attacking both the knight on e5 and the pawn on g2. }
6... Bd6
{ Black has no problems in this line, even after White's central break. } 7. d4
exd4 8. cxd4 Bg4 { The pin is not very pleasant for White. } 9. dxc5 Bxc5
{ Black has an excellent game. } *

