1. e4 c5 2. c3
{ The Alapin has always bothered me a lot. It is very difficult for Black to create fighting opportunities. }
2... e5
{ The line that I suggest is extremely rare compared to  2...d5  and  2...Nf6  . I think is nice to have this line in our repertoire, because is less known and objectively Black is fine as well. }
3. Nf3 Nc6 4. Bc4 { The main and the most dangerous move. } 4... Nf6 5. Ng5
{ Clearly the critical line. } 5... d5 { The only way to defend on f7. } 6.
exd5
{ This particular position with the pawns on c2 and c7 is one of the main theoretical positions in the Italian. Now things are a bit different. }
6... Nxd5
{ The critical position for the whole line. White has many tempting ideas but I believe Black is doing well in all of them.   Worse is  6...Na5  In the Italian this is the best move, here it is not the same.  7.Bb5+  Bd7  8.Qa4  and White is better. }
7. Nxf7 { Without 7.d4 is much less dangerous for Black. } 7... Kxf7 8. Qf3+
Ke6 { The only move. Protecting the knight on d5. } 9. d4 Na5
{ The key move! Black wants to remove the powerful bishop from c4. } 10. Bg5
Qd7 11. Nd2 cxd4 { Black can defend successfully. } *

