1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 d6 { This is the move for Najdorf Players. } 3. Bb5+
{ Not a very ambitious line. } 3... Bd7 4. Bxd7+ Qxd7 5. d4 cxd4 6. Qxd4 Nc6 7.
Qd3
{ White's main idea is to develop simply with Nf3 and short castle, and then to jump on d5 with the knight from c3. I believe with very simple moves, Black will be able to equalize. }
7... g6 { The best way to develop. } 8. Nf3 Bg7 9. O-O Nf6 10. Nd5 O-O 11. Bg5
{ Black has a few good moves here at his disposal. } 11... Ne8
{ Preparing ...e6. There is nothing wrong with  11...Nxd5  12.exd5  Ne5  13.Nxe5  Bxe5  14.Rae1  Rfe8=  Shimanov, A @@StartBracket@@2597@@EndBracket@@ - Cheparinov, I @@StartBracket@@2667@@EndBracket@@ Tornelo INT 2021. }
12. Rad1 e6 13. Ne3 h6 14. Bh4 f5 { The strongest continuation for Black. } 15.
exf5 gxf5 { The central pawns can potentially be very dangerous. } *

