[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 d6 { This is the move for Najdorf Players. } 3. Nge2
{ A tricky move order. } 3... Nf6 4. h3
{ A little too artificial. Black has different ideas available. } 4... e5
{ Closing the center. Now White will never play d4. } 5. Ng3
{ A perfectly sound move, with the idea of continuing with Bc4. } 5... a6
{ A good point is to stop some ideas connected to Bb5+. } 6. Bc4
{ If  6.a4  then  6...Be6  and Black has an easy game. } 6... b5 7. Bd5 Ra7
{ Black is threatening ...b4. } *

