1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 d6 { This is the move for Najdorf Players. } 3. Nge2
{ A tricky move order. } 3... Nf6 4. g3 { White wants to postpone d4 for now. }
4... Nc6 5. d4 { Entering the Open Sicilian with g2-g3. } 5... cxd4 6. Nxd4 g6
{ Transpose to the Dragon with 6.g3.   Quite dangerous is  6...Nxd4  7.Qxd4  g6  in view of  8.e5!?  dxe5  9.Qxd8+  Kxd8  10.Bg2  . }
7. Nde2 { This is considered to be the best option for White. } 7... Bg7 8. Bg2
O-O 9. O-O Rb8
{ The best move. The other options are  9...Bd7  and  9...a6  . } 10. a4
{ It seems normal to include this move, trying to prevent ...b5. In case of  10.Nd5  b5  11.c3  b4  Black is doing very well. }
10... a6 11. Nd5 b5 12. axb5 axb5
{ 12...Rxb5!?  it's weird, but also interesting. } 13. Bg5
