1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 Nbd7 7. Bc4 Qb6 8.
Bb3 e6 9. Qd2 Be7 10. O-O-O Nc5 11. Qe2
{ Not the most accurate. White wants to continue with f4 and e5.   The main line is:  11.f3 }
11... h6
{ Better was:  11...Qc7!  12.f4  b5  13.e5  dxe5  14.fxe5  Nd5  The point is that the bishop on g5 is hanging with check.  15.Bxe7  Nxe7⇆ }
12. Bh4 Qc7 13. f4 O-O { 13...b5?  Now is bad in view of  14.e5 } 14. e5 dxe5
15. fxe5 Nh7
{ The knight on h7 is very passive.   Black had to play  15...Nxb3+!  16.Nxb3  Nd5  17.Nxd5  exd5  18.Bxe7  Qxe7  19.Rxd5  Be6  20.Rd6  Rfe8∞  With enough compensation for the pawn. }
16. Bxe7 Qxe7 17. Ne4 b5 18. Nxc5
{ A very strange move. White exchanges his best piece.   Much better was:  18.Nd6!  Bb7  19.h4±  Black's position is difficult. }
18... Qxc5 19. h4 { The next moves are quite easy for Black. } 19... Rd8 20. c3
Bb7 21. Rh3 b4 { Black is already much better. } 22. Bc2 Rac8 23. g4
{ White is too late. } 23... Qa5 24. cxb4 Qxa2 25. Nb3 Bd5
{ White cannot defend from the numerous threats. } 26. Rc3 Rxc3 27. bxc3 Qa3+
28. Kb1 Rc8 29. Bxh7+ Kxh7 30. Qc2+ Kg8 31. Nc5 a5 32. Rxd5 exd5 33. e6 fxe6
34. Qg6 Rf8 35. Qxe6+ Kh8 *

