1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be3 e6
{ This was the main weapon of Topalov for many years. } 7. f3 b5 8. a3 h5
{ Black stops g4. } 9. Qd2
{ Probably better now is to go with short castle  9.Be2 } 9... Nbd7 10. O-O-O
Bb7 11. Kb1 Rc8 12. h3 { The other moves are:  12.Be2  and  12.Bd3 } 12... h4
13. Bd3 Ne5 14. Rhe1 Be7 15. Bg5 Nc4 16. Bxc4 Rxc4 17. Nb3 Rh5 18. Bxf6 gxf6
{ Playing for a win, as always.   Stronger was  18...Bxf6!  19.Qxd6  Qxd6  20.Rxd6  Bxc3  21.bxc3  Rxc3  22.Na5  Bc8  23.Nc6  Bd7⩲ }
19. Qe3 { Better was  19.f4! } 19... Qc7 20. Rd3 a5
{ Black had to play  20...b4!  21.axb4  Rxb4 } 21. Qd2
{ Much stronger was  21.Qe2!  b4  22.f4!  Rh8  23.Nb5  Qb6  24.Nxd6+  Bxd6  25.Rxd6  Qxd6  26.Qxc4  Ba6  27.Qc5  Qxc5  28.Nxc5  Bb5⩲  with some advantage for White in the endgame. }
21... b4 22. axb4 Rxb4 23. Na2 Rb6 { White is in big trouble now. } 24. Rd1 a4
25. Nd4 Ba6 26. Ra3 Qb7 27. c3 d5 28. Rxa4 dxe4 29. fxe4 Qxe4+ 30. Qc2 Bb7 31.
Rd2 Qxc2+ 32. Kxc2 f5 33. Nf3 Be4+ 34. Kd1 Bg5 35. Re2 Rd6+ 36. Ke1 Bf4 37. Nd4
Bg3+ 38. Kf1 e5 *

