1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 Nf6 4. Nc3 cxd4 5. Nxd4 a6 6. Be2 e5 7. Nb3 Be7 8. Be3
Be6 9. Nd5 Nbd7 10. Qd3 O-O 11. c4 { More popular nowadays is:  11.O-O } 11...
b5 12. cxb5 { The safest move.  12.Nd2 } 12... axb5 13. O-O Bxd5 14. exd5 Nb6
15. Qxb5 { Better was  15.Bxb6  Qxb6  16.Qxb5  Qa7=∞ } 15... Nbxd5 16. Bd2
{ Black's central pawns can be very strong in the future. } 16... Rb8 17. Qd3
Qd7 18. Rfd1 Nb4 19. Qg3 Ne4 20. Qf3 d5 { White is in big trouble. } 21. Bxb4
{ The best defensive resource was  21.a3!  Nc2  22.Rac1  Rfc8  23.Bb4  Nxb4  24.Qxe4⩱  with some hopes to survive. }
21... Rxb4 22. a3 Ng5 { The key move! } 23. Qe3 Re4 24. Qd3 Rb8 25. Rac1 g6
{ It is very difficult to play as White here. } 26. Nc5 Bxc5 27. Rxc5 Rd4
{ Better than taking on b2. } 28. Qc2 Ne6 29. Rc3 Rxd1+ 30. Bxd1 Nd4
{ A huge mistake in the time trouble.   More accurate was:  30...d4! } 31. Qc1
{ Suddenly White is back in the game. } 31... Kg7 32. h4 h5 33. b4 Qe7 34. Rc7
Qf6 35. Rd7 Qf5 36. Qc7 { Returning the favour. Better was.  36.Qg5! } 36...
Re8 37. Qb7 { 37.Rxd5?  Qe4-+  Winning a piece. } 37... Re6
{ White cannot defend the king now. The queen is too far. } 38. f3
{ 38.Qxd5  Rf6  39.f3  Qd3-+ } 38... Rf6 39. Qxd5 Qd3 40. Ba4 Qe3+ 41. Kh2 Ne2
*

