{ I decided to show this blitz game too. These days even in online blitz strong players are playing their main weapons. }
1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+ Bd7 4. Bxd7+ Qxd7 5. c4 e5
{ The modern setup.   The main theory is:  5...Nf6  6.Nc3  Nc6  7.d4  cxd4  8.Nxd4  Nxd4 }
6. O-O { Maybe better is to start with  6.Nc3  Nc6  7.d3 } 6... Nc6 7. a3 Be7
8. Nc3 Bd8 { The main idea! } 9. Nd5 Nge7 10. d3 O-O
{ Black has a very easy game. } 11. b4 cxb4 12. Nxb4 f5
{ I would prefer  12...Bb6!? } 13. exf5 Nxf5 14. Bb2
{ An inaccuracy. Safer is  14.Nxc6  Qxc6  15.Qb3= } 14... Bb6 15. Nd5 Bc5
{ The bishop is very powerful. } 16. Qd2 { Better was  16.Nd2 } 16... Rf7
{ Of course more accurate was first:  16...h6! } 17. Rae1 { 17.Ng5! } 17... h6
18. Re2 Raf8 { Sooner or later Black will push g5-g4 } 19. a4 Qd8 20. Bc3 g5
{ Stronger was  20...Nh4!  21.Nxh4  Qxh4∓ } 21. Re4 Nh4
{ Looks good but in fact is not clear at all. } 22. Rxh4 gxh4 23. Qxh6 Rh7 24.
Qe6+ Kh8 25. h3 { White definitely has compensation. } 25... Qc8 26. Qg6
{ The decisive mistake. I would play  26.Qxc8  Rxc8  27.Nf6=∞ } 26... Rxf3 27.
Nf6 Rxf6 28. Qxf6+ Kg8 29. Re1 Qf8 30. Qe6+ Qf7 31. Qc8+ Kg7 32. Qg4+ Kh8 33.
Re2 Nd4 34. Re4 Ne6 35. Re2 Qf6 36. Kh1 Rg7 37. Qh5+ Kg8 38. Qe8+ Nf8 39. f3
